  finance  minister  arun  jaitely  has presented  three  budgets  he  has  promised  of  doubling  the  farmers  income  in  the next five years i havent seen any clear roadmap being laid out in this regard this year  farmers  have  shown  resilience  and  agriculture  growth  is  expected  at  41  per cent the  finance  minister  has  glossed over the prevailing  crisis by  promising to bring in a model law for contract farming he has also announced the farm credit outlay  being  enhanced  to  rs  10  lakh  crore  but  what  is  lesser  known  is  the  fact that bulk of the farm credit for which an interest subvention scheme of 3 per cent is provided if paid back in time is availed by the agriculture business companies there  was  no  acknowledgement  of  the  terrible  agrarian  crisis  that  prevails  in  the budget  two  years  of  backtoback  drought  and  the  unannounced  hit  by demonetisation has certainly accentuated the farm crisis and needed an immediated relief   